# Java formatting and imports

This project does not yet use Spotless or a shared `formatter.xml`. Follow consistent style from existing files (4 spaces, K&R braces, ~120 char lines).

## Imports — required

1. **Every type** used in code must have an `import` (or live in the same package).
2. **Remove unused imports** after every edit.
3. **Never** use a fully qualified class name when a simple name works **without** a collision.

## Import order

`java.*` / `javax.*` → third-party → `dev.vepo.stomp4j.*`

## Name collision (only exception)

Import one type; use FQN for the other:

```java
import java.util.List;

public void merge(List<String> ids, dev.vepo.stomp4j.server.Session session) { ... }
```

## Before finishing Java changes

1. `ReadLints` on edited paths — fix unused-import warnings and unresolved types.
2. Full gate: [static-analysis.mdc](static-analysis.mdc) (`mvn verify`).
